            <br/>
            <h3>Why even bother watching this?</h3><br/>
			<p>The humour in the show is top-notch, relying heavily on witty banter, pop culture references, and hilarious visual gags. The writing is clever and keeps the jokes fresh and unpredictable, making it a joy to watch from start to finish.</p>
            <p>What sets this series apart from other high school comedies is its ability to tackle serious topics in a lighthearted way. The show addresses issues such as bullying, peer pressure, and social anxiety, but never loses its comedic edge.</p>
            </br>
            <h3>Animation:</h3><br/>
			<p>The animation style is simple yet effective, with a colorful and vibrant color palette that adds to the overall cheerful tone of the series. The music is also catchy and memorable, perfectly complementing the upbeat and energetic vibe of the show.</p>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/10.gif" style="max-height: 43vh; max-width: 90%; display: block;"></center><br/>           
            </br>
            <h3>Conclusion: </h3><br/>
            <p>Overall, "Daily Lives of High School Boys" is a must-watch for fans of slice-of-life comedies. Its witty writing, lovable characters, and clever humour make it a standout in the genre and a truly enjoyable viewing experience. It will remind you of friends from your high school days, and make you reminisce of the times you spent with them.</p>
